y had been largely abandoned. Why that happened is one of the questions that Sergei Khrushchev seeks to answer in this book, as he draws on archival records, memoirs, and his own personal recollections to provide a comprehensive account of the 1961-1964 period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHeads of statezSoviet Union. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aShriver, George.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078424440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637376140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626373761423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626373761/original  a978-3-11-078424-4  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK